                            <comment id="12580513" author="ruwan" created="Wed, 19 Mar 2008 19:40:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue is not with the user defined values for the mail transport but google (gmail) sending the contentType as text/plain (I hope you have used gmail to send the mail) and missing a null check in the code. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now it is fixed on the svn head. Please verify.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12595962" author="evanthika" created="Mon, 12 May 2008 03:24:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The NullPointerException did not occur when the e-mail was sent. However the response message was not received. This issues has been reported as a separate issue.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-297&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-297&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tested on 1.2_QA_B1. The issue will be closed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
